## Open WebUI Tools

This repo documents how I configure [Open WebUI](https://github.com/open-webui/open-webui) using tools and how I create my own custom tools.  
It is meant as a reference for myself and for anyone who wants to reuse or learn from my setup.

---

### Goals of this project

- **Centralize configuration**: Keep all my Open WebUI tool definitions and configuration in one place.
- **Share custom tools**: Show how I build and organize my own tools (Python/Node/script-based, etc).
- **Document my workflow**: Explain how I use these tools day‑to‑day in Open WebUI.

---

### Project structure

_Currently:_

- **`README`**: This file. High-level documentation of the project and tools.

_Current/typical layout:_

- **`tools/`**: Source code for my custom tools.
  - **`youtube_transcript.py`**: Tool to fetch YouTube transcripts.
- **`config/`**: Open WebUI tool configuration files (YAML/JSON/etc).
- **`examples/`**: Example calls, prompts, and usage notes.

I will update this section as the repo grows.

